PROJECT TITLE:
Google Translator Project
This is a simple Google Translator project using Python. It leverages the googletrans library to translate text from one language to another seamlessly.

TABLE OF CONTENTS:

1. [Installation]
2. [Usage]
3. [Contributing]
4. [Contact]
5. [Acknowledgments]


INSTALLATION:

To install the necessary dependencies and set up the project, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repository:
    bash
    git clone https://github.com/SahanashreeTalagade/Google-Translator-Project.git
    
2. Navigate to the project directory:
    bash
    cd GoogleTranslatorProject
    
3. Install the dependencies:
    bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    

USAGE:

To use the translator, run the main.py script. Hereâ€™s how you can do it:

1. Open your terminal or command prompt.
2. Navigate to the project directory.
3. Run the following command:
    bash
    python main.py
    

Modify the text and dest_language variables in main.py to translate different text or to different languages.

CONTRIBUTING:

If you would like to contribute to this project, please follow these steps:

1. Fork the repository.
2. Create a new branch (git checkout -b feature-name).
3. Make your changes and commit them (git commit -m 'Add new feature').
4. Push to the branch (git push origin feature-name).
5. Create a pull request.

